{
  "name": "Armbar",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "modules/pf1spheres/assets/icons/spheres/wrestling.webp",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>When you successfully maintain a grapple against a creature you have already pinned, you may expend your martial focus as an immediate action to attempt to damage one of the creatures limbs; the creature must succeed at a Fortitude save or have one of its limbs damaged by you (arms, legs, tentacles, or wings), ending the grapple. The penalties for a damaged limb are identical to the effects of a removed limb from the Limb Ripper talent except as follows:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The creature suffers no bleed damage.</li>\n<li>Any numerical penalties associated with the limb are halved.</li>\n<li>The condition lasts for 1 round plus 1 round per 4 points of base attack bonus you possess.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Undead are not immune to this effect and must make the saving throw.</p>\n",
